# MindShift Architecture

This is a portfolio project. Every file should reflect real engineering judgment — clean separation of concerns, consistent patterns, and proper error handling throughout.

---

## Project Structure

```
lib/
  core/
    ai/           # ClaudeService — all AI calls
    constants/    # AppColors, AppSpacing, AppTextStyles, AppStrings
    firebase/     # FirestoreService — all Firestore access
    router/       # GoRouter config
    services/     # FCMService, DeepLinkService
    theme/        # AppTheme
    utils/        # AppDateUtils, Validators
    widgets/      # Shared reusable widgets
  features/       # One folder per feature (screen + sub-widgets)
  models/         # Pure data classes — no Flutter/Firebase imports
  providers/      # Riverpod providers only
  main.dart
```

**Rule:** Features never import from other features. Cross-feature coordination goes through `providers/`.

---

## State Management (Riverpod)

### Provider types — use the right one

| Use case | Provider type |
|----------|--------------|
| Firebase stream (auth, profile) | `StreamProvider` |
| Mutable list/state (goals, habits, affirmations) | `StateNotifierProvider` |
| Singleton service (Firestore, Claude, FCM) | `Provider` |
| Derived / computed value | `Provider` or `select` |

### `StateNotifier` pattern — all mutable feature state follows this exactly

```dart
class GoalsNotifier extends StateNotifier<List<Goal>> {
  final Ref _ref;

  GoalsNotifier(this._ref) : super([]);

  // Load from profile stream — called by the provider setup
  void _loadFromProfile(UserProfile? profile) {
    if (profile != null) state = profile.goals;
  }

  Future<void> addGoal(Goal goal) async {
    final uid = _ref.read(authStateProvider).valueOrNull?.uid;
    if (uid == null) return;

    // Optimistic update — state first, then persist
    final updated = [...state, goal];
    state = updated;
    await _ref.read(firestoreServiceProvider).updateUserField(uid, {
      'goals': updated.map((g) => g.toJson()).toList(),
    });
  }
}

final goalsProvider = StateNotifierProvider<GoalsNotifier, List<Goal>>((ref) {
  final notifier = GoalsNotifier(ref);
  // Sync on stream changes AND on initial read
  ref.listen(currentUserProfileProvider, (_, next) {
    next.whenData((profile) => notifier._loadFromProfile(profile));
  });
  ref.read(currentUserProfileProvider).whenData(
    (profile) => notifier._loadFromProfile(profile),
  );
  return notifier;
});
```

**Rules:**
- Always do optimistic update (mutate `state` before `await`)
- Always guard with `if (uid == null) return`
- Never call Firestore or ClaudeService directly from a widget — always through a notifier or provider
- Computed getters (e.g. `List<Goal> get activeGoals`) belong on the notifier, not in the widget

