## Data Layer (`FirestoreService`)

`FirestoreService` is the single point of Firestore access. No widget or provider touches `FirebaseFirestore.instance` directly.

### Collection strategy
- `users/{uid}` — entire `UserProfile` document (goals, habits, affirmations, completions, etc. are all fields)
- `journals/{entryId}` — separate collection (high write volume, large docs)
- `chat_sessions/{sessionId}` — separate collection

### Persistence pattern for profile sub-lists
```dart
// Partial update — prefer updateUserField for sub-lists
await firestore.updateUserField(uid, {
  'goals': goals.map((g) => g.toJson()).toList(),
});

// Full merge — use updateUserProfile for multi-field changes
await firestore.updateUserProfile(updatedProfile);
```

