## Models

All models are **pure Dart** — no Flutter or Firebase imports.

### Required structure for every model

```dart
class Goal {
  // 1. All fields final — models are immutable
  final String id;
  final String title;

  // 2. const constructor with named params and sensible defaults
  const Goal({required this.id, required this.title, this.status = 'active'});

  // 3. copyWith — every field optional
  Goal copyWith({String? id, String? title, String? status}) => Goal(
    id: id ?? this.id,
    title: title ?? this.title,
    status: status ?? this.status,
  );

  // 4. fromJson — always provide fallbacks, never force-cast
  factory Goal.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => Goal(
    id: json['id'] as String,
    title: json['title'] as String,
    status: json['status'] as String? ?? 'active',  // nullable with default
  );

  // 5. toJson — include all fields
  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() => {'id': id, 'title': title, 'status': status};

  // 6. Computed getters are fine — they're pure
  bool get isCompleted => status == 'completed';
}
```

**Rules:**
- No mutable fields (`var`, `late` without `final`)
- `fromJson` fallbacks for every nullable/optional field — never let a missing Firestore field crash the app
- Use `(json['field'] as num?)?.toDouble()` for numbers — Firestore may return int or double

