## Error Handling

### Async gaps in widgets
```dart
// Always check mounted after any await
Future<void> _submit() async {
  await someAsyncOperation();
  if (!mounted) return;       // ← required before any context/ref use
  context.go('/next');
}
```

### Notifiers
Notifiers swallow errors silently only when there is a reasonable fallback. Otherwise surface to the UI.

```dart
// Bad — silent failure with no user feedback
try {
  await firestore.updateUserField(uid, data);
} catch (_) {}

// Good — optimistic update already applied; log for debugging
try {
  await firestore.updateUserField(uid, data);
} catch (e) {
  debugPrint('GoalsNotifier.addGoal failed: $e');
  // Re-throw or show snackbar if the failure matters to UX
}
```

### AI errors in UI
Show `ErrorState` widget or an inline error banner with a Retry button — never a silent empty list.

