## Widget Rules

**Widgets are dumb — they render state and dispatch actions:**
```dart
// Good
onPressed: () => ref.read(goalsProvider.notifier).deleteGoal(goal.id),

// Bad — business logic in widget
onPressed: () async {
  final uid = FirebaseAuth.instance.currentUser!.uid;
  await FirebaseFirestore.instance.collection('users').doc(uid).update(...);
},
```

**`ConsumerWidget` vs `ConsumerStatefulWidget`:**
- Use `ConsumerWidget` by default
- Use `ConsumerStatefulWidget` when you need: `AnimationController`, `TextEditingController`, `FocusNode`, `initState` logic, `_starterTriggered` flags

**BuildContext across async gaps:**
Always add `if (!mounted) return` after any `await` before accessing `context` or `ref`.

